terpret customer feedback as it applies to recipes Update online recipe cards Have an innate love of food and cooking You are ... Exceptionally skilled in copy editing, proofreading, and ensuring adherence to style guides A judicious editor; you are capable of distilling complex company initiatives into accessible copy for home cooks Highly organized with supreme attention to detail. You'll triple confirm and cross-check until you know beyond a shadow of a doubt that it's correct! Able to meet extremely tight deadlines while ensuring complete accuracy across all projects and tasks A self-starter and truly proactive problem solver who works relentlessly to execute all steps needed until the problem is resolved Proficient in Google Docs, Microsoft Word, Google Sheets, Excel, project management software, and content management systems At a minimum, you have ... Bachelor's degree in English, Journalism, or a Communications-related field 3-5 years experience in editing, writing, and content creation Background in food editorial required; familiarity with recipe writing standards is an asset You'll get \u2026 Competitive Salary & 401k company match that vests immediately upon participation Generous parental leave of 16 weeks & PTO policy $0 monthly premium and other flexible health plans effective first day of employment 75% discount on your subscription to HelloFresh (as well as other product initiatives) Snacks, cold brew on tap & monthly catered lunches Company-sponsored outings & Employee Resource Groups Collaborative, dynamic work environment within a fast-paced, mission-driven company It is the policy of HelloFresh not to discriminate against any employee or applicant for employment because of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, age, marital status, genetic information, disability or because he or she is a protected veteran. ",
